    <h3><a name="1"></a>Nov 20 (3 posts):  <a href="http://docs.FreeBSD.org/cgi/getmsg.cgi?fetch=8998+0+current/freebsd-advocacy">About the Symbolism</a></h3>

    <p>Here we have <a href="mailto:posonsky@iname.ru">[Stanislav
      Posonsky]</a> asking us about the d&brvbar;mon logo, which he
      refers to as an "impish creature", and whether or not we should
      give up this "devilry" in favor of a more neutral symbol for our
      logo/image.</p>

    <p><a href="mailto:will@physics.purdue.edu">[Will Andrews]</a>
      replied, letting Stanislav know that this has been discussed
      <strong>MANY</strong> times, and gave us a nice explanation of why
      we like the d&brvbar;mon, and why we keep it.</p>

    <blockquote>
      <p><i>It is not an impish creature.  It's a daemon, which is a
	generic name for a server process, such as Apache, or inetd, or
	syslogd, etc.  The fork the daemon wields refers to the fork()
	system call.  As you can see, there is no relationship between
	Satanic images and our mascot.</i> - <a
	href="mailto:will@physics.purdue.edu">[Will Andrews]</a></p>
    </blockquote>

    <!-- 2 -->

    <hr noshade>

    <h3><a name="2"></a>Nov 13 - Nov 16 (15 posts):  <a href="http://docs.FreeBSD.org/cgi/getmsg.cgi?fetch=19509+0+archive/2000/freebsd-advocacy/20001119.freebsd-advocacy">accessing portal site</a></h3>

    <p>Well, it seems we still haven't stopped discussing why this
      <a href="12.html#1">original post</a> shouldn't have been Cc'd
      to -advocacy.  A few good quotes this week:</p>

    <blockquote>
      <p><i>It's plain common sense to not Cc advocacy.  Apart from the
	unwanted implication that you're a spokesman for FreeBSD
	advocacy, there is a danger of the recipient of your mail
	getting submerged in a deluge of -advocacy replies.  Luckily,
	that didn't happen in this case.</i> - [<a
	href="mailto:Rahul.Siddharthan@ltp.ens.fr">Rahul
	Siddharthan]</a></p>
    </blockquote>

    <blockquote>
      <p><i>No, he's just trying to get you to stop sending email that
	has the appearance of collusion with the FreeBSD Project.  If
	you want to send a "heads up" to a FreeBSD mailing list use BCC
	so the person or company you're sending the mail to will not
	misconstrue your message as coming from or being approved by the
	FreeBSD Project or Advocacy group.</i> - <a
	href="mailto:wes@softweyr.com">[Wes Peters]</a></p>
    </blockquote>

