    <h3><a name="4"></a>Nov 16 - Nov 19 (5 posts): <a href="http://docs.FreeBSD.org/cgi/getmsg.cgi?fetch=101803+0+archive/2000/freebsd-advocacy/20001119.freebsd-advocacy">Good BSD press in feedmag</a></h3>

    <p><a href="mailto:des@ofug.org">[Dag-Erling Smorgrav</a> sent us a
      <a href="http://www.feedmag.com/essay/es405_master.html">url</a>
      with this quote:</p>

    <blockquote>
      <p><i>The underground's latest heroes are the directors of
	software projects based on 4.4BSD Lite, the free operating
	system pioneered at the University of California at Berkeley in
	the late 1970s.  The gratis software churned out by projects
	like FreeBSD and OpenBSD is in arguably superior to most
	mainstream Linux distributions, both in terms of security and
	portability.</i></p>
    </blockquote>

    <p>However, I declined to follow the link due to the bad reviews
      that followed as replies.  You decide for yourself.</p>

